      "parallelizable": false,
      "conceptual_summary": "find_quasi_periodic_events. Scans a 1D numerical signal to identify the indices of regularly recurring, salient local maxima. The process involves signal conditioning to reduce noise and amplify periodic components, followed by a peak-finding algorithm that filters candidates based on temporal proximity constraints derived from the sampling rate.. Applications: Detecting periodic dimming events in a star's light curve data to locate transiting exoplanets., Identifying recurring aftershock patterns in seismic sensor data following a major earthquake., Analyzing vibration data from a rotating machine to find harmonic frequencies indicative of mechanical imbalance or wear., Locating seasonal spikes in a time-series of consumer purchasing data to model economic cycles.",
